ADDITIONAL PERMISSION FOR SINGLE-TENANT SELF-HOSTED DEPLOYMENTS
(pursuant to GNU AGPL v3, Section 7)

As an additional permission under Section 7 of the GNU Affero General
Public License version 3, operators who deploy this software on their own
Cloudflare account solely to serve their own home or commercial inspection
business ("single-tenant self-hosted deployments") are granted permission
to operate modified versions of this Program — including allowing their
clients to interact with the Program through a network interface — without
being required to make the source code of those modifications available to
those clients, provided that:

  (a) The deployment serves only the operator's own inspection business
      (i.e., one legal entity's inspectors and their clients).

  (b) The operator does not offer the Program, or any modified version of
      it, as a hosted or managed service to third parties (i.e., does not
      provision separate workspaces, accounts, or instances of the Program
      for multiple independent businesses or individuals for a fee or
      otherwise).

If condition (b) is not met — that is, if you offer this software as a
managed or hosted service to multiple independent tenants — the standard
terms of the GNU Affero General Public License v3 apply in full, including
the network interaction requirement of Section 13.

This additional permission may be removed by a downstream licensee at
their option.
